title: For Sale:  (SOLD PENDING FUNDS) Colt Python 6" From Colt's Custom Shop - NIB- From 1978
postcontent:
I purchased this Python from the long defunct JPL Guns in Lawrence, Kansas in 1985. It came out of Colt's Custom Shop in 1978 and was in JPL's glass case marked "Personally Owned Firearm - Not For Sale." That sticker is still affixed to the well-worn original Colt Box. Of course, since it was marked not for sale I had to try to buy it. It took the trade of two other fine handguns and a cash hand of poker to walk out the door with it. I will be glad to provide a sworn letter to the buyer with the complete story if desired. It has sat in my safe now for 28 years. In that span of time I've owned a total of four different Pythons, a couple of Trooper Mk IIIs and a couple of Detective Specials, and as fine a revolvers as they all are, none come close to the action on this one. And no matter what angle or lighting is used, the camera simply cannot capture the incredible deep beauty that was Colt's Royal Blue at that time. There are many more pictures available; just email for them.

I'm old now, and I am simply not ever going to take this gun out and shoot it. I suppose there are still some fine unfired Pythons out there, but probably few like this one. How to say this in the most polite possible way: I'll be using the funds to enhance my granddaughter's college account, so please don't waste my time and yours with low ball offers or trades, I am not interested and they will be ignored. I figure I will probably need to list this revolver on Gunbroker to get its value but I decided to try Armslist locally first. If you're looking at Armslist from outside Colorado, yes, I will ship this gun from my dealer to yours at extra cost. Thanks for taking the time to read this listing.

AR-15 Hammer and Trigger Pin Dimensions: 
Some Colt® AR type rifles have been manufactured with hammer and trigger pins and holes which are approximately .176" in diameter. These are referrend to as "large pin" Colts. The box is excellent with a few wear marks on the edges, no paperwork came with the gun and no accessories. The light colored walnut checkered grips are also excellent. title: Want To Buy:  1911 Government Frame with premium features
postcontent:
I am looking to buy a complete 1911 government FRAME (receiver, lower, etc) with the following features. This project is an effort to get my girlfriend into shooting and needs to be executed accordingly, so please excuse my sounding picky. If in doubt, please send me pictures--worst I can do is say no!

I will consider both series 70 and 80 frames.

Features I need, i.e. do not want to pay a gunsmith to have put in:
Beavertail grip safety with appropriately shaped hammer
High grip cut below trigger guard (either a round style like the Colt Enhanced or DE1911 frame, or a straight cut like the Caspian Basic or new Ithaca frame)

Features I really want and would pay extra for:
Checkered frontstrap (not serrated or anything else, checkered only)
Single side extended thumb safety, or an ambi safety that does not require ambi cut on grips

Features that are nice but not essential:
3-hole match trigger
Checkered mainspring housing
Higher profile mag release

The frame and parts should be in decent condition (no rust or pitting, finish wear is ok) and reasonably well fitted (original factory is fine) and in working order, with the exception of the slide stop and grips. Your frame does NOT need to have either of those parts or a slide. I will of course consider guns that have them, but I won't pay much extra.

Budget is flexible and completely depends on what is offered, but is approximately in the $300 to $700 range. Interested in anything nationwide, local would just be a plus. I will pay for shipping to my FFL.

I also have for trade a Kahr PM9 with a black slide and accessories, and a scoped Remington 541T.

Check out this Ithaca frame for a good example of the key features I want.
